🧠 What is a REST API?

A **REST API (Representational State Transfer)** is a way for:

👉 Client (frontend) to communicate with server (backend)

Example:

```text
React App → API → Database → Response
```

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 HTTP Methods in REST API

| Method | Purpose     |
| ------ | ----------- |
| GET    | Fetch data  |
| POST   | Create data |
| PUT    | Update data |
| DELETE | Remove data |

---

🔷 Example API Endpoints

```text
GET     /users
GET     /users/:id
POST    /users
PUT     /users/:id
DELETE  /users/:id
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Setup Express Server

```javascript
const express = require("express");
const app = express();

app.use(express.json());

app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log("Server running on port 3000");
});
```

---

🔷 Sample Data

```javascript
let users = [
  { id: 1, name: "John" },
  { id: 2, name: "Sara" }
];
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 GET All Users

```javascript
app.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  res.json(users);
});
```

---

🔷 GET Single User

```javascript
app.get("/users/:id", (req, res) => {
  const user = users.find(u => u.id == req.params.id);
  res.json(user);
});
```

---

🔷 POST (Create User)

```javascript
app.post("/users", (req, res) => {
  const newUser = {
    id: users.length + 1,
    name: req.body.name
  };

  users.push(newUser);
  res.json(newUser);
});
```

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 PUT (Update User)

```javascript
app.put("/users/:id", (req, res) => {
  const user = users.find(u => u.id == req.params.id);

  if (user) {
    user.name = req.body.name;
    res.json(user);
  } else {
    res.status(404).send("User not found");
  }
});
```

---

🔷 DELETE User

```javascript
app.delete("/users/:id", (req, res) => {
  users = users.filter(u => u.id != req.params.id);
  res.send("User deleted");
});
```

